They say motion sickness from games and VR can be overcome by repeated exposure, just like the same from boats, trains, etc. I used to throw up every time I got on a train as a kid, now I read during my trips without a care in the world. It might very well be the level of detail that's bothering you, if Dusk's low poly style gets to you as well. There's less to judge distance and relative motion by in those games, and so your brain might get confused. Try Half-Life: Souce, the Source port of HL, and see if you can play it as well as HL2 (same engine), or if it also gets to you. If it does, then the best you can do is to get used to it little by little until you hopefully learn to deal with it. Oh, and a stable 60+ FPS will help.
